 :tx/rationale "Create task: AR-2: Schema + trace producer — :recon/* attributes and post-command trace writer in main.rs (INV-STORE-014, INV-GUIDANCE-024). BACKGROUND: Every command already loads the store (layout.load_store()) and produces CommandOutput JSON. The trace producer adds a post-command step: extract spec refs from the JSON, run spec_graph_neighbors(), write :recon/trace datom. INV-STORE-014 already mandates every command produces a transaction — the trace extends this to read commands. APPROACH: (1) Schema: add :recon/trace-refs (String, Many) — spec ref IDs found in command output. :recon/trace-neighbors (String, Many) — entity idents of related entities from graph traversal. :recon/trace-neighborhood (String, One) — the dominant spec namespace of the trace. :recon/trace-command (String, One) — the command name that produced this trace. (2) In main.rs, after commands::run() and before rendering: call produce_recon_trace(store, &cmd_output.json, cmd_name) -> Option<Vec<Datom>>. If the JSON contains parseable spec refs (INV-*/ADR-*/NEG-*), run spec_graph_neighbors and write trace datoms. If no spec refs found, skip (no trace for spec-free commands). (3) Write trace datoms via layout.write_tx(). This is the SAME write path as harvest and session-start. (4) Performance budget: <1ms total. AVET lookup is O(1), VAET reverse-ref is O(1), BFS depth 2 on typically <10 neighbors. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid task create with INV-INTERFACE-001 in title produces :recon/trace datom. (B) braid status (no spec refs in output) produces no trace. (C) Trace datom contains correct spec refs and neighbor idents. (D) Performance: trace adds <1ms (measured via --verbose timing). DEPENDS-ON: AR-1. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs + crates/braid/src/main.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs"
